Package com.pranab.playwithgraphs

Interface Graph<V,​K>

Type Parameters:
V - The relational entity type, that will be used as vertex in vertex-edge mapping ,
K - Unique key to identify a Vertex
All Known Subinterfaces:
DirectedGraph<V,​K>, DirectedWeightedGraph<V,​K,​W>, UnDirectedGraph<V,​K>, UnDirectedWeightedGraph<V,​K,​W>, UnWeightedGraph<V,​K>, WeightedGraph<V,​K,​W>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AdjacencyListDirectedWeightedGraph, AdjancencyListUnDirectedWeightedGraph, AdjencyListDirectedGraph, AdjencyListUnDirectedGraph
public interface Graph<V,​K>
An Object that helps in realization of data in Vertex Edge(Graph) format.

Vertex : The entity that is to be related with another entity.

Edge : Relationship between the entities.

Graph Definition: A set of items connected by edges. Each item is called a vertex or node. Formally, a graph is a set of vertices and a binary relation between vertices, adjacency.

Author:
Pranab Bharadwaj
